<subSubSection id="A0CBE85CB1F75CA6567D22134D969A3D" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" type="notes">
<paragraph id="69E5F3D61FA41553268B409717DCE76B" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1AFF0A038D71BDB5C573118FD0D98C7" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName id="A3B1ECC0236910932190A44FC8D9DEEB" class="Sordariomycetes" genus="Dendrostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrostoma aurorae" order="Diaporthales" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aurorae">Dendrostoma aurorae</taxonomicName>
was discovered on stems of dying chestnut trees and appears morphologically similar to the chestnut blight pathogen, 
<taxonomicName id="6FFE0C04D09946DCC70D58BBC6DDCC2F" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cryphonectriaceae" genus="Cryphonectria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cryphonectria parasitica" order="Diaporthales" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="parasitica">Cryphonectria parasitica</taxonomicName>
. However, these two diaporthalean pathogens can be distinguished by the existence of a central column inside the conidiomata of 
<taxonomicName id="6DC18DF9F7C383B8628DA746FFB39417" class="Sordariomycetes" genus="Dendrostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrostoma aurorae" order="Diaporthales" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aurorae">Dendrostoma aurorae</taxonomicName>
. In the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A841E29EBE88D139F53AB58D6B297A77" class="Sordariomycetes" genus="Dendrostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrostoma" order="Diaporthales" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Dendrostoma</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="59D4A6C4EF960E329333FA935C9CDC10" genus="D." lsidName="D. aurorae" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="aurorae">D. aurorae</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="01B172DFCBD7ACA18E939CD2CB9A8E95" genus="D." lsidName="D. chinensis" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="chinensis">D. chinensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="ED4CE1B4083531079F14AC80A5C3B436" genus="D." lsidName="D. shandongense" pageId="6" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="shandongense">D. shandongense</taxonomicName>
by the existence of an obvious central column.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
